What you are looking for is a Spring [constructor dependency injection][1].
There are 3 ways to inject your dependency in Spring: **class field**, **contructor** and by a **setter method**. 

The best and recommanded way is the constructor dependency injection.
In your case, you have to set an `@Autowired` annotation on your constructor (which is not mandatory since Spring 4.3) and remove the `@Autowired` annotation from your field `private TesseractService tesseractService;`.

