The UI (Main) thread is synchronous. If you have background threads the data should be posted to the UI thread before UI is changed, at that point all calls are synchronous. The application may crash/freeze if you attempt to update UI elements from a thread other than main.

Here is an example of runnable setting a background thread to UI (Main) thread . Note that &quot;application&quot; variable is Context. Research Android View Model, LiveData and Observers for other examples.

    if (application != null &amp;&amp; object != null){
            Handler mainHandler = new Handler(application.getMainLooper());
            Runnable myRunnable = () -&gt; {
                tokenLiveData.setValue(object);
            };
            mainHandler.post(myRunnable);
        }

